= Shotdetect

== Shotdetect is a free software (LGPL) which is able to detect shots and scenes in a movie.

The result produced is a simple XML file containing all the informations about the movie generated.

== Example
Put the file you want to analyse in the same directory of shotdetect (it not mandatory but itâ€™s easier with the command line)


~~~
{from a shell}
shotdetect -i myvideo.avi -o output_dir -s 60 -w -v -f -l -m -r
~~~
== Options details
\-s : set threshold\n
The threshold is the level for shot detection. High will not detect a lot, low will detect a lot of false shots. A good choice is about 60.

\-w : generates audio xml information\n
See the generated file for more details\n

\-v : generates video xml informations\n
See the generated file for more details\n

\-f : generates the first image of shots\n
\-l : generates the last image of shots\n
\-m : generates the thumbnails images\n
\-r : generates the real size images\n
